TI  == coinfection of fusobacterium nucleatum and actinomyces israelii in mastoiditis diagnosed by next-generation dna sequencing.
AB  == some bacterial infections involve potentially complex mixtures of species that can now be distinguished using next-generation dna sequencing. we present a case  of mastoiditis where gram stain, culture, and molecular diagnosis were nondiagnostic or discrepant. next-generation sequencing implicated coinfection of fusobacterium nucleatum and actinomyces israelii, resolving these diagnostic discrepancies.
