TI  == myocardial infection due to fusobacterium nucleatum.
AB  == fusobacterium nucleatum is an anaerobic gram-negative bacillus, which inhabits the oropharynx, gastrointestinal tract, and female genital tract. infections classically affect the head and neck. we report a patient with a myocardial mass  due to f. nucleatum, initially thought to be a neoplasm, and discuss anaerobic cardiac infections.
