PMID== 22875742
TI  == fusobacterium nucleatum infection mimicking metastatic cancer.
AB  == a 48-year-old man presented with fevers, chills, weight loss, multiple liver masses, and several superficial and deep venous thromboses in lower extremities.  cancer work up was negative. a liver biopsy grew fusobacterium nucleatum. to our  knowledge, f. nucleatum infection presenting with multiple liver masses and trousseau-like syndrome has not been reported earlier.
