TI  == use of a novel assay to evaluate enzymes that produce hydrogen sulfide in fusobacterium nucleatum.
AB  == to evaluate enzymes that produce hydrogen sulfide (h(2)s) in species of fusobacterium nucleatum, we developed an assay based on sds-polyacrylamide gel electrophoresis with renaturation followed by active staining. this assay provided precise insight into the enzymes that produce h(2)s in terms of their number and molecular weights.
