PMID== 18337385
TI  == thoracic vertebral actinomycosis: actinomyces israelii and fusobacterium nucleatum.
AB  == actinomyces spp. are considered rare pathogens in today's medicine, especially with thoracic vertebral involvement. classic actinomycosis (50%) presents as an oral-cervicofacial ("lumpy jaw") infection. this report describes a case of spinal cord compression caused by actinomyces israelii with the coisolation of fusobacterium nucleatum. there are limited numbers of similar cases.
