PMID== 12400529
TI  == fusobacterium osteomyelitis in a child with sickle cell disease.
AB  == children who have sickle cell disease are at increased risk for osteomyelitis caused by salmonella spp. and staphylococcus aureus. we report a case of anaerobic osteomyelitis caused by fusobacterium nucleatum in a child with sickle  cell disease. the infection did not resolve with antibiotic therapy alone, but was cured after surgical debridement and hyperbaric oxygen therapy.
