TI  == infective endocarditis due to fusobacterium nucleatum in an intravenous drug abuser.
AB  == infective endocarditis due to anaerobic non-spore-forming gram-negative bacilli in intravenous drug abusers is exceedingly rare, with only two cases being previously reported in the literature. a case of endocarditis due to fusobacterium nucleatum in an intravenous drug abuser is reported, accompanied by a review of the literature.
