PMID== 1602152
TI  == fusobacterium nucleatum bacteraemia with multiple liver abscesses in an hiv-i antibody positive man with igg2 deficiency.
AB  == liver abscess formation due to fusobacterium nucleatum is rare. we describe an hiv-i antibody positive man, with normal surrogate markers of cell-mediated immunity, who presented with f. nucleatum bacteraemia and liver abscess formation. he was found to have igg2 subclass deficiency. this case illustrates the clinical importance of altered b-cell function in patients who are at an early stage of hiv disease.
