TI  == osteomyelitis of the pelvis due to fusobacterium nucleatum.
AB  == anaerobic pelvic osteomyelitis occurs rarely in children. a case of fusobacterium nucleatum osteomyelitis of the right ilium [correction of ileum] in a child without apparent risk factors is described. this case emphasizes the value of diagnostic aspirates. therapy with a combination of intravenous and oral clindamycin led to successful resolution of the infection.
