PMID== 2624558
TI  == interleukin-1 and interleukin-1 inhibitor production by human adherent cells stimulated with periodontopathic bacteria.
AB  == this study examined the effect of the putative periodontopathic bacteria bacteroides gingivalis and fusobacterium nucleatum on the production of interleukin-1 (il-1) and il-1 inhibitors by human plastic-adherent mononuclear cells from normal donors. fusobacterium mortiferum was used as a non-oral, non-pathogenic control organism. unstimulated adherent cells spontaneously secreted an il-1 inhibitor, whereas stimulation with b. gingivalis induced the synthesis and secretion of il-1. with both fusobacteria il-1 was present in the intracellular environment, whereas the predominant secretory product was either il-1 or an il-1 inhibitor. these results suggest that bacteria are capable of modulating cytokine production by monocytes and may thereby alter the local immune response.
