TI  == outer membrane protein pattern of eubacterium plautii.
AB  == the outer membrane sds-page pattern of eubacterium plautii was characterized by a large number of surface exposed low- and high-molecular-mass proteins. silver stainable carbohydrate was not present. the pattern was clearly distinct from those of outer membrane preparations of eubacterium saburreum and fusobacterium nucleatum. the results are compatible with a gram-positive cell wall structure in e. plautii.
