PMID== 830651
TI  == chemical structure of the lipid a component of lipopolysaccharides from fusobacterium nucleatum.
AB  == the lipid a component of lipopolysaccharides from fusobacterium nucleatum fev 1 consists of beta-1',6-linked d-glucosamine disaccharides, which carry two phosphate groups: one in glycosidic and one in ester linkage. the amino groups of the glucosamine disaccharides are substituted by d-3-hydroxyhexadecanoic acid. the hydroxyl groups of the disaccharide backbone are acylated by tetradecanoic, hexadecanoic, and d-3-hydroxytetradecanoic acids. part of the ester-bound d-3-hydroxytetradecanoic acid is 3-o-substituted by tetradecanoic acid. whereas a similar pattern of fatty acids was detected in lipopolysaccharides from two other f. nucleatum strains, the amide-bound fatty acid in f. varium and f. mortiferum was d-3-hydroxytetradecanoic acid. the chemical relationships of lipid a from fusobacteria and other gram-negative bacteria are discussed.
TIHT== 
